AI Mock Interview Platform
Overview

The AI Mock Interview Platform is a full-stack web application that helps students practice technical interviews using Artificial Intelligence.
The system generates interview questions based on the user's resume, allows voice-based answers, and provides detailed feedback after the interview.

This platform helps users improve their interview performance by practicing in a realistic interview environment.

Features
Resume-based interview question generation
AI-powered interviewer
Voice-based question and answer system
Live coding challenges
Automatic interview feedback and scoring
Interview history tracking
Technologies Used
Frontend
React
JavaScript
CSS
Axios
Backend
Node.js
Express.js
MongoDB Atlas
Mongoose
AI & APIs
Google Gemini API
AssemblyAI (Speech-to-Text)
Murf AI (Text-to-Speech)
Project Structure
AI-Mock-Interview/
│
├── client/        # Frontend React application
├── server/        # Backend Node.js application
└── README.md
Installation
1. Clone the repository
git clone <repository-url>
cd AI-Mock-Interview
2. Install dependencies

Frontend

cd client
npm install

Backend

cd server
npm install
Environment Variables

Create a .env file inside the server folder.

PORT=5000
MONGODB_URI=your_mongodb_connection_string
JWT_SECRET=your_secret_key
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key
ASSEMBLYAI_API_KEY=your_assemblyai_api_key
MURF_API_KEY=your_murf_api_key
Run the Project

Start backend server:

cd server
node server.js

Start frontend:

cd client
npm run dev

Open in browser:

http://localhost:5173